</problem>
</exercise>
<figure id="BRI_APUSH_08_06_RailSplit" class="full-width">
<media id="fs-idm393914528" alt="The cartoon shows Johnson sitting on top of a globe beside a large needle and thread. Across the United States, running south to north, there is a seam. Johnson says, “Take it quietly Uncle Abe and I will draw it closer than ever!” Lincoln holds a rail up under the globe to keep it in place. Lincoln says, “A few more stitches Andy and the good old Union will be mended!” The caption at the bottom reads, “The ‘Rail Splitter’ at work repairing the Union.”">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/BRI_APUSH_08_06_RailSplit.jpg"/>
</media>
<caption>The “Rail Splitter” at Work Repairing the Union, 1865, a cartoon drawn by Joseph E. Baker.</caption>
</figure>
